news.title: Germany's Geschaeftshaus am Gendarmenmarkt files for insolvency
news.para: The tower, described on its website as an "essential part of the Frankfurt skyline", is home to part of Germany's central bank and to Deka, one of its biggest asset managers.

news.title: Shimao Group sweetens debt revamp terms ahead of liquidation hearing: Sources
news.para: Shimao will on Wednesday face its first court hearing into the liquidation petition filed by state-owned lender China Construction Bank (Asia) over unpaid loans of HK$1.58 billion ($201.75 million).

news.title: Ambuja Cements, Ravi Sanghi to sell 3.52% stake in Sanghi Industries
news.para: The promoters proposed to sell 90,92,000 shares representing 3.52% of the total issued and paid-up equity share capital.

news.title: Amitabh Bachchan buys more office properties in Mumbai's Andheri suburb
news.para: The actor already owns four offices totalling over 12,000 sq ft built up and 10,800 sq ft carpet area in the same commercial tower.

news.title: Kolkata: Metro service on New Garia to airport corridor to be extended soon
news.para: ​While train services along the 5.40 km stretch from New Garia (Kavi Subhash) to Ruby More (Hemanta Mukhopadhyay) stations have already become functional, another 4.39 km stretch extending up to Beleghata has got the clearance after careful evaluation of all safety parameters required for commissioning.

news.title: Nashik civic body to approve development related projects worth Rs 400 crore
news.para: The civic body’s various departments, including public works, health, water supply, mechanical, town planning, and property, have initiated the process of drawing up proposals for developmental works related to their respective areas.

news.title: Goa government may soon allow sand mining in CRZ
news.para: State govt urged the Centre to allow sand extraction from sand bars for construction activities as there is a shortage of the commodity due to the ban on its extraction in Goa.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government to set up development authority for Shahjahanpur
news.para: Chief minister Yogi Adityanath, who is also the housing minister, held a meeting with senior officials of the department in Lucknow on Monday.

news.title: Registration of sale deeds for apartments in Bhubaneswar resumes after two years
news.para: There was a deadlock of deed registration for apartments since May 2022, which was imposed by the Orissa high court taking into view a petition, which has brought attention to gross violation being attempted in the activities bypassing the set frame of rules and regulation.

news.title: Howrah in total mess with land grab & illegal buildings: West Bengal CM
news.para: ​Numerous plots in Howrah and Bally municipal areas were being illegally occupied and high-rises were being built along narrow roads without following regulations, leaving no space for ambulances or fire trucks, said Banerjee during her meeting.

news.title: Noida airport delayed by six months as steel import hit
news.para: The completion of the mega project has been pushed back by at least six months to April 2025. Officials said the delay was because of the slow progress in the construction of the terminal building, which is running way behind schedule.

news.title: Buyers struggle to find home under Rs 1 crore in Hyderabad, narrate house-hunting ordeal
news.para: Industry insiders believe that prices will not fall until development is decentralised to other parts of the city like north and east Hyderabad.

news.title: Supertech submits plan to Uttar Pradesh government for completion of stuck projects
news.para: Supertech has stated that its total dues to the bank and development authority amount to about Rs 8,000 crore, while project receivables from both launched and yet-to-be-launched projects exceed Rs 14,000 crore, making the projects' net worth positive.

news.title: Lenders of Jaiprakash Associates raise apprehension on settlement proposal
news.para: ​During the proceedings of the NCLAT, counsel appearing for lenders said the insolvency plea was filed against JAL in 2017 and for the last seven years, it dragged it under the pretext of a settlement.

news.title: Ambuja Cement bags 24 limestone mines in FY24
news.para: ​​This is in addition to 1 billion tonnes of reserve of Sanghi Industries, a Saurashtra-based company which billionaire Gautam Adani-owned firm acquired last November at an enterprise value of Rs 5,185 crore.

news.title: Kaisa Group liquidation petition adjourned by Hong Kong court
news.para: The Shenzhen-based developer has been working to restructure its offshore debt for two years after defaulting on $12 billion in offshore debt in late 2021.

news.title: Need to make changes in building byelaws in Uttar Pradesh: CM
news.para: ​While talking about the development of the hotel industry at a meeting with senior officials of the housing department, Adityanath said it is the result of efforts to encourage the tourism potential that today the state has emerged as the first choice of tourists.

news.title: Birla Estates acquires 16.5 acres land in Pune
news.para: The land parcel has a development potential of approximately 32 lakh sq ft and an estimated revenue potential of Rs 2,500 crore.

news.title: Only 195 projects set up grievance redressal cell despite MahaRERA directive
news.para: The regulator has undertaken a review of the same and is now planning to initiate action against the developers that are not in compliance with the directive issued in August 2023 with an objective of resolving homebuyers’ grievances.

news.title: Belagavi civic body forms fact-finding panel to identify its properties
news.para: According to the corporators of BCC, more than 95 properties belonging to the corporation have been given on lease and rent basis to government and private organisations that are into social service.
